HARD RULE — ASK THE UE VERSION FIRST: Before authoring or editing ANY material graph, you MUST ask the user which UE version they are targeting, and confirm that version is supported (a nodes-ue<version>.json DB pair exists in agent-pack/). Do not write any .matgraph.json until the UE version is confirmed and supported. Set the graph's `ueVersion` to that confirmed version.

For UE5 material work, follow agent-pack/SPEC.md and only use node types from the version-matched DB agent-pack/nodes-ue<version>.json (plus the reserved types MaterialOutput/FunctionInput/FunctionOutput/MaterialFunctionCall). Write each material to its own project folder: `graphs/<project>/<material_name>.matgraph.json` plus any MaterialFunctions it uses as siblings in the same folder. Connections use "node:pin" strings. Never write x/y positions.

Material Functions: if a material calls an MF by UE asset path, look it up under functions[<assetPath>] and use its inputs[].name/outputs[].name for connections — official /Engine/... MFs in the committed agent-pack/enginemf-index-ue5.7.json, the user's own /Game/... MFs in agent-pack/workmf-index.json. If it is not in the matching index, stop and ask the user to run the matching crawl (Engine MF for /Engine/..., WorkMF for /Game/...) — do not invent pin names. See SPEC.md "Work-project Material Functions".
